.TH LCALL 1 "January 2026" "lcall 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lcall \- call selected libc functions from the command line
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lcall
.I func
.RI [ key = value " ...]"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B lcall
is a minimal command-line utility that allows calling a small, fixed set
of selected libc functions directly from the shell.

It is intended as a lightweight bridge between shell scripts and POSIX APIs,
without using interpreters, scripting languages, or persistent daemons.

Arguments are passed as
.BR key=value
pairs. Only simple argument types such as strings and integers are supported.
.SH FUNCTIONS
.TP
.B getaddrinfo
Resolve a host and service name into network addresses.
.RS
.TP
Arguments:
.TP
.B node
Hostname or address string.
.TP
.B service
Service name or port number (optional).
.TP
.B afamily
Address family filter: \fB4\fP for IPv4, \fB6\fP for IPv6 (optional).
.RE
.TP
.B getnameinfo
Convert a numeric IP address into a host and service name.
.RS
.TP
Arguments:
.TP
.B addr
IPv4 or IPv6 address.
.TP
.B service
Service or port (optional).
.RE
.TP
.B if_nametoindex
Convert a network interface name to its index.
.RS
.TP
Arguments:
.TP
.B name
Interface name (e.g. \fBeth0\fP).
.RE
.TP
.B if_indextoname
Convert a network interface index to its name.
.RS
.TP
Arguments:
.TP
.B index
Interface index.
.RE
.SH EXAMPLES
Resolve a hostname:
.PP
.nf
lcall getaddrinfo node=example.com service=80
.fi
.PP
Resolve IPv6 only:
.PP
.nf
lcall getaddrinfo node=example.com afamily=6
.fi
.PP
Reverse lookup:
.PP
.nf
lcall getnameinfo addr=8.8.8.8
.fi
.PP
Interface name to index:
.PP
.nf
lcall if_nametoindex name=lo0
.fi
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 on success.
On error, a non-zero value is returned and an error message is printed
to standard error.
.SH NOTES
.B lcall
is not a general-purpose foreign function interface.
Only explicitly implemented functions are available.
